text: Leucopogon foliosus is a plant in the family Ericaceae native to Western Australia. It was first described in 2016 by Michael Hislop. The species epithet, foliosus ("leafy", "many-leaved") describes the leafy inflorescence. ==References== foliosus Category:Ericales of Australia Category:Flora of Western Australia
title: Leucopogon foliosus
